Linear Regression method¶

. . .

In [120]:
def gradientDescent(x, y, theta, alpha, m, numIterations):
    xTrans = x.transpose()
    for i in range(0, numIterations):
        hypothesis = np.dot(x, theta)
        loss = hypothesis - y 
        cost = np.sum(loss ** 2) / (2 * m)
        print("Iteration %d | Cost: %f" % (i, cost))
        # avg gradient per example
        gradient = np.dot(xTrans, loss) / m 
        # update
        theta = theta - alpha * gradient
    return theta

Stochastic Gradient Descent¶

.

In [117]:
# Take only 1 instance
def stochasticgradientDescent(x, y, theta, alpha, m, numIterations):
    xTrans = x.transpose()
    for i in range(0, numIterations):
        rindex = np.random.randint(1,8000+1)
        hypothesis = np.dot(x[rindex], theta)
        loss = hypothesis - y[rindex]
        cost = np.sum(loss ** 2) / (2 * 1)
        print("Iteration %d | Cost: %f" % (i, cost))
        # avg gradient per example
        gradient = np.dot(xTrans[:,rindex], loss) / 1
        # update
        theta = theta - alpha * gradient
    return theta
